-- MOVES-Orrick, Herrington & Sutcliffe hires Konstantin Kroll 
-- 
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 03:14PM EDT
-- None



Aug 4 (Reuters) - Orrick, Herrington & Sutcliffe LLP appointed Konstantin Kroll as a partner in its M&A and private equity practice group at its Moscow office.

Kroll, who is joining from Jones Day, has advised on some of the largest M&A and PE transactions in the energy, manufacturing, consumer and banking sectors in the Russian market, the company said.   Orrick is a leading global law firm focused on advising companies in the infrastructure, finance and tech sectors.